<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-29T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6363/453: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cox</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-29T13:00:00-04:00">August 29, 1936—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>179. My 177, August 28, 5 p.m. Standard Oil Co. today tells me it has
                            just signed temporary agreement together with Shell-Mex which does not
                            obligate companies to accept marketing arrangement. Commission informs
                            oil companies that final date for their acceptance of the latter is
                            September 22.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cox</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>